node.text:
Morocco blues via @delafuentecam 💙 Share your photos with us and we will post them in our account. Apply for a feature following the link in our bio: @earthfever

Spotted in the north-western Rif mountains in Morocco, Chefchaouen is famous for its stunning blue-shaded buildings and cobbled streets that has given the nickname “The Blue Pearl”.

Visitors get lost in the Chefchaouen Medina, looking for recreation and relaxation, shopping souvenirs at the bazaars, dine at a rooftop restaurant tasting the Traditional Moroccan Cuisine and learn about their history at the Kasbah Museum.

📸 @delafuentecam
📍 Chefchaouen, Morocco

node.text:
Norway views from Mt. Bispen ⛰ Wanna see your pictures posted in our account? Apply for a feature on earthfever.net (link in my bio: @earthfever) 

The views of these Norwegian mountains from top of Bispen (The Bishop) rise steep above the famous Trollstigen road and Isterdalen valley. These mountains attracks climbers, hikers and basejumpers. The prime hiking season is July through September, and you don't have to be a mountain climber to reach the summits. However, a good portion of mountain experience will be useful.

Would you dare to hike this mountain? 👇

📽 @ellisivbrain
📍Mt Bispen, Trollstigen, Norway
